{{Infobox person |name = Chandra Kaluarachchi | other_names = |image_size = 200px |image= |alt = |caption = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1943|04|6}} |birth_place = Narahenpita [[Sri Lanka]] |death_date = |death_place = |death_cause = |resting_place = |resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|display=inline,title}} --> |nationality = [[Sri Lanka]]n |education = |years_active = |party = |spouse = Lakshman Wijesekara |children = |awards = |signature = |website = |footnotes = | occupation = Film ,Television , Radio and Stage actress }}
'''Chandra Kaluarachichi''' (born April 6, 1943) is a [[Sri Lanka]]n actress. Since her debut role as 90-year-old woman in ''Raththaran putha'' by Arnold Wickramasuriya in 1962,<ref name=" Arnold ">{{cite news| title = Handahana with Arnold Wickramasuriya | publisher =Daily News(Sri Lanka:| url= http://archives.dailynews.lk/2005/10/19/arts02.htm}}</ref> Chandra has become recognized for playing motherly and other figures on stage, film, radio and television serials.<ref name="Ahasin Wetunu Minissu">{{cite news | title = R R Samarakone's life comes in a biography | publisher = Daily News(Sri Lanka: | url = http://www.dailynews.lk/features/r-r-samarakones-life-comes-biography | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131227155839/http://www.dailynews.lk/features/r-r-samarakones-life-comes-biography | archivedate = 2013-12-27 | df = }}</ref>
== Biography ==
=== Early life and education === Chandra Kaluarachichi grew up in [[Narahenpita]], near Colombo. Her early touches with nature In the meantime The program named Lamapitiya was encouraged to pursue acting in radio. After leaving college she played the leading role in several Sri Lankan stage productions. Dramatist Premaranjit Tilakaratne A House without a roof ' he identifies produced 'Wahalak Neti Geyak'. It got a recognition at the State Drama Festival 1964 winning awards for the Best Actress as Chandra Kaluarachchi.<ref name="Wahalak Neti Geyak">{{cite news| title = 'The Father' and the 'Ghosts' adopted for the Sinhala stage| publisher = sundayobserver (Sri Lanka)| url = http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2007/01/21/imp06.asp| access-date = 2013-12-27| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20131227191540/http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2007/01/21/imp06.asp#| archive-date = 2013-12-27| dead-url = yes| df = }}</ref> Chandra Kaluarachchi played a grandmother in the S. Karunaratne play ''Erabadu Mal Pottu Pipila'' in 1967.<ref name=" Erabadu Mal Pottu Pipila ">{{cite news| title = A Critique on the State Sinhala Drama Festival of 1966 | publisher = dailynews.lk (Sri Lanka)| url = http://archives.dailynews.lk/2007/11/14/art04.asp}}</ref> Dayananda Gunawardena’s Gajaman Puwatha, first in the genre of "docudrama", which he introduced to the Sinhala stage on 14 October 1975. It is colorful figure of Ranchagoda Lamaya was acted by her<ref name=" Gajaman Puwatha">{{cite news| title = Synthesis of literature and spectacle| publisher = island.lk (Sri Lanka)| url = http://www.island.lk/2006/10/28/satmag3.html}}</ref>
