{{Infobox film | name = Daddy Issues | image = File:Daddy Issues 2018.jpg | caption = Theatrical release poster | director = Amara Cash | producer = Jenna Cedicci | story = {{Plainlist| * Amara Cash * Alex Bloom }} | screenplay = Alex Bloom | starring = {{Plainlist| * Madison Lawlor * Montana Manning * Andrew Pifko }} | music = {{Plainlist| * Maxton Waller * Patrick Ridgen }} | released = 2018 | cinematography = Nico Aguilar | editing = Amara Cash | studio = Under 1 Roof Productions | runtime = 88 minutes | country = United States | language = English }} '''''Daddy Issues''''' is an American [[indie film]] directed by Amara Cash about a 19-year-old "queer pixie" who becomes ensnared in a [[love triangle]] after falling for a gender-fluid online crush. The film was screened at multiple film festivals and received many accolades.
==Cast== * Madison Lawlor as Maya Mitchell * Montana Manning as Jasmine Jones * [[Andrew Pifko]] as Simon Craw * Monte Markham as Gordon Craw
==Screenings== ''Daddy Issues'' premiered in 2017 and was subsequently screened at: * Arizona Underground Film Festival (2018)<ref name=AZUFF/> * Boston LGBT Film Festival (2018)<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Boston Underground Film Festival|url=https://bostonunderground.org/2018/03/buffwicked-queer-2018/|title=BUFF@Wicked Queer 2018|accessdate=1 June 2018}}</ref> * Fort Myers Film Festival (2018)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fortmyersfilmfestival.com/2018OfficialGuide.pdf|title=2018 Fort Myers Film Festival|publisher=Fort Myers Film Festival|accessdate=1 June 2018}}</ref> * [[Inside Out Film and Video Festival]] (2018)<ref name=InsideOut>{{cite web|title=2018 Toronto LGBT Film Festival Schedule|url=https://www.insideout.ca/torontofestival/film/daddy-issues|publisher=Inside Out|accessdate=1 June 2018}}</ref> * [[Film Festival International]] in London and Nice (both 2018)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmfestinternational.com/11th-screening-room-1-nice-iff-2018/|title=May 11th Screening Room 1|publisher=Nice Filmmaker Festival|accessdate=1 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=LondonFilmmaker/> * MidWest WeirdFest (2018)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.midwestweirdfest.com/news/2018/3/15/midwest-weirdfest-2018-winners-announced|publisher=MidWest WeirdFest|accessdate=1 June 2018|title=MidWest WeirdFest 2018 Winners Announced!}}</ref> * Northern Virginia International Film Festival (2018)<ref name=NovaFilm/> * SOHO International Film Festival (2018)<ref>{{cite web|publisher=SOHO Film Fest|url=https://www.eventbrite.com/e/soho9-daddy-issues-us-feature-l-new-york-premiere-tickets-45824745046|title=#SOHO9: "Daddy Issues" (US Feature)|accessdate=1 June 2018}}</ref> * Outfest Los Angeles LGBTQ Film Festival (2018) <ref name="outfest">{{cite web |title=Outfest Los Angeles |url=http://www.outfest.org/filmguide/daddy-issues-2/ |accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref>
==Reception== The film was hailed as a "dark romance with a tender heart" at the 2018 [[Inside Out Film and Video Festival]] in [[Toronto]], [[Canada]], whose reviewers lauded Amara Cash for her "vision, style, and twisted sense of humour".<ref name=InsideOut/> ''Punch Drunk Critics'' also gave the film – which it described as an "exquisitely messed up [and] beautiful nightmare" – a positive review, awarding it 4 out of 5 stars for, among other things, its "fascinating and deeply disturbing script" and "visual style".<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Punch Drunk Critics|url=http://www.punchdrunkcritics.com/2018/04/nova-film-festival-review-daddy-issues.html?m=1|title=NOVA Film Festival Review: 'Daddy Issues'|date=14 April 2018|accessdate=2 June 2018}}</ref>
