{{Infobox person | name =Karin Hübinette | image = Karin Hübinette in August 2013.jpg | alt = <!-- descriptive text for use by the blind and visually impaired's speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software --> | caption =Hübinette in 2013 | birth_name = Ragnhild Maria Hübinette | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1966|4|18|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Sollentuna Municipality|Sollentuna]], [[Sweden]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | death_place = | nationality = Swedish | other_names = | occupation = Television presenter, journalist | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = | spouse = | children = | parents = | relatives = }}
'''Karin Ragnhild Maria Hübinette''', née Pettersson (18 April 1966), is a [[Swedes|Swedish]] journalist and television presenter. She is the sister of politician [[Hillevi Engström]].<ref name="medievarlden.se">{{cite web|url=http://www.medievarlden.se/nyheter/2014/03/karin-huebinette-tillbaka-till-agenda|title=Karin Hübinette tillbaka till Agenda|publisher=|accessdate=6 April 2016}}</ref> Hübinette started her career as the presenter of the debate show Svart eller vitt, which was broadcast on [[TV4 (Sweden)|TV4]] in the mid-1990s.<ref name="sydsvenskan.se">{{cite web|url=http://www.sydsvenskan.se/kultur--nojen/karin-hubinette--tillbaka-med-egen-agenda/|title=Karin Hübinette – tillbaka med egen agenda|work=Sydsvenskan|accessdate=6 April 2016}}</ref> After that she presented [[Uppdrag granskning]] and Kvällsöppet, and was also a reporter at [[Sveriges Radio]]. She then worked solely for [[SVT]] presenting the news shows [[Agenda (Swedish TV program)|Agenda]] and [[Aktuellt]]. She is a board member of the company Hands on AB.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.solidinfo.se/foretag/hands-on-i-stockholm-ab/personer|title=Hands on i Stockholm AB|publisher=|accessdate=6 April 2016}}</ref>
When her sister [[Hillevi Engström]], who is a politician for the [[Moderate Party]], became secretary of employment after the general elections in 2010, Hübinette had to resign from her work as a journalist at Agenda and Aktuellt.<ref name="medievarlden.se"/> She however remained working at SVT, where she became a foreign reporter for the show Korrespondenterna.<ref>[http://www.expressen.se/nyheter/karin-hubinette-far-nytt-jobb/ Karin Hübinette får nytt jobb] Expressen Retrieved 6 April 2016</ref> One year later she started presenting her own talk show, called ''Hübinette'', which aired for two seasons in 2011 and 2012.<ref name="sydsvenskan.se"/>
Karin Hübinette returned to presenting Agenda in 2014 after the program changed format and added [[Camilla Kvartoft]] and others as presenters.<ref name="svt.se">{{cite web|url=http://www.svt.se/kultur/hubinette-atervander-till-agenda|title=Hübinette återvänder till Agenda|work=svt.se|accessdate=7 April 2016}}</ref> This means that if her sister appears on the show, one of the other presenters can interview her.<ref name="svt.se"/>
