==Box Office Poison== In 1938 a [[Box Office Poison (magazine article)|list]] was published of stars who were considered "box office poison" by exhibitors. The list was from Harry Brandt of the Independent Theater Owners Association.<ref>Louella O. Parsons' Close-Ups and Long-Shots of the Motion Picture Scene The Washington Post (1923-1954) [Washington, D.C] 25 June 1939: A3.</ref>
The stars included: *[[Edward Arnold (actor)|Edward Arnold]] *[[Fred Astaire]] *[[John Barrymore]] *[[James Cagney]] *[[Joan Crawford]] *[[Dolores del Río]] *[[Marlene Dietrich]] *[[Kay Francis]] *[[Greta Garbo]] *[[Katharine Hepburn]] *[[Norma Shearer]] *[[Mae West]]
==''Variety''{{'}}s Over Priced Stars of 1968== In 1968 ''Variety'' magazine published a list of ten stars it considered overpriced. The stars charged at least $250,000 a film and had at least four flops in a row recently:<ref>{{Cite news |last=Browning |first=Norma Lee |date=5 July 1968 |title=Are Marlon, Yul, Natalie on the Way Out? |url=https://chicagotribune.newspapers.com/image/376678092/ |work=[[Chicago Tribune]] |page=b10 |subscription=yes}}</ref>
* [[Brigitte Bardot]] * [[Marlon Brando]] * [[Yul Brynner]] * [[Tony Curtis]] * [[Glenn Ford]] * [[James Garner]] * [[William Holden]] * [[Rock Hudson]] * [[Anthony Quinn]] * [[Natalie Wood]]
